<C>__{susan}
<D>__{no. we don't.}
<A>__{they drift, osmotically, into the library in awkward silence.}
<C>__{susan }
<D>__{brave you had a chance to look at dad's rare books? jefferson's parliamentary manual, a first edition bleak house }
<A>__{joe comes closer, takes a deep breath.}
<C>__{joe}
<D>__{i love your smell.}
<C>__{susan}
<D>__{ i guess you haven't.}
<A>__{now susan, close to joe, leans closer, her nose in joe's neck. joe holds himself very still.}
<C>__{susan }
<D>__{i like your smell, too.}
<C>__{joe}
<D>__{thank you.}
<C>__{susan}
<D>__{it was everything.}
